#Repost @sosapproachtofeeding (@get_repost)
・・・
Being able to maintain a stable position is incredibly important foundational skill set for being a successful feeder. Many #children struggle with postural stability during #mealtimes, which negatively impacts their ability to attend to the task of #eating, process the #sensoryinput, #selffeed and get their mouth to work correctly to chew up and swallow foods. 
Even if postural stability isn't a challenge for the child in other areas of their life, most seating arrangements #families use during mealtimes do not set children up for success. During mealtimes at home, most children are seated in #highchairs, #boosterseats, #sassyseats (pictured here) or adult sized #chairs that provide them with no foot support (a very important part of your base of support). When you have no foot support it is incredibly challenging to maintain a still seated posture-this is why so many #kids fidget in their chairs all throughout the mealtime! 
Typically, our first recommendations to families is to get their child in a stable seating arrangement to decrease the amount of brainpower and energy they have to put into keeping themselves upright in the chair during mealtimes. This frees them up to focus on the complex task of feeding themselves and eating.

One of the easiest ways to start providing additional support to a child during mealtimes is to give them a footrest. You can do this by purchasing them a new chair (I.e. Adjustable wooden chair) or simply modifying their current seating arrangement by fashioning a foot rest out of materials you have around the house- laundry hampers turned upside down, step stools, or old phone books or text books wrapped in duct tape (pictured here)! #pickyeater #pickyeaters #feedingtherapy #toddlermeals #momlife #dadlife #toddlermealtime #blw #familymeal #therapylife #tubefed #gtube

Gustav Neumann, Lobecek, Czechoslovakia. Gustav was born in a ten-house village in 1860. He married Louisa Deutschova in 1883 and they had three children. Gustav built a small business into the largest manufacturer of women’s dresses and men’s work clothes in central Europe. Soon after the occupation his children Artur and Ota escaped, only to be killed by the Germans in Yugoslavia. Gustav was take to Terezin in 1942 then transported to Treblinka, where he was murdered upon arrival. .

Breakfast in bed might be lovely. Carnations are nice too. But a family getaway to Charleston is a perfect way to celebrate mom, especially with the little ones in tow. Mornings can be spent strolling under towering oak trees. In the afternoons, head to the beach where the kids can collect seashells while mom sits back and enjoys the show. It’ll be a weekend of peace, not always quiet, but a whole lotta love––just the way she likes it. Happy Mother’s Day.
⠀⠀
Whether you have a vacation mom who takes pictures of everything, or a vacation mom who loves a long morning walk, we want you to know that we celebrate you today, and everyday.

Amina H. Aban works with the Bangsamoro Development Agency (BDA), the development arm of a revolutionary organization, to bring #infrastructure projects to conflict-affected communities in #Mindanao, Southern #Philippines. As the daughter of a revolutionary leader, a man she saw just three times before he was killed, Amina knows the price #families in Mindanao have had to pay due to #conflict. "What my father was fighting for is for everyone. What I’m doing is my contribution to that. My father and I want the same things, we just chose a different path to help out people." #eastasiapacific #peace #community #development

It's FriYAY! Pick up the phone and call someone you love ♥️☎️
Healthy benefits to picking up the phone instead of texting:
🔴Calling is so much more personal
🔴A call takes more time so the person knows you were really thinking of them
🔴You can hear the tone in voices, not texts... and feel excitement, energy and love
🔴Auto correct can make a caring text complicated and scrabbled, which can be frustrating & embarrassing, since we are usually rushed the text does not come across with the same meaning as a good old fashion phone call (yes guilty)
